body_html:
My bad, some stuff got swapped out. This should be the steps to run it, I'll update the issue too. (These
assume that pytorch is already installed)

git clone https://github.com/blester125/baseline.git
cd baseline
git checkout speed-test
cd python
./install_dev.sh baseline no-test
echo "{}" > mead/config/mead-settings.json
mead-train --config config/conll-bio.json

This should both print timing information to stdout and also to a file called timing-{pid}.log
